# UI Components

**When** you are creating or modifying UI elements in the application

**Then** always use native Filament components such as `x-filament::icon`, `x-filament::button`, `x-filament::dropdown`, and `x-filament::avatar`. For separators in dropdowns, use `div` with class `border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 my-1`. Avoid using non-existent components.

**Because** this ensures consistency in UI/UX, leverages Filament's built-in accessibility, and maintains a cohesive look across the application.

**Examples**

```blade
# ✅ Corretto
<x-filament::button>Click Me</x-filament::button>

# ❌ Non Corretto
<x-ui.button>Click Me</x-ui.button>
```

## Riferimenti
- [Documentazione Filament](https://filamentphp.com/docs/3.x/support/blade-components/overview)
- [Memoria UI in Cursor](../memories/ui-components.mdc)
